  "text": "Another possible effect of dysfunctional and depleted CD4+ T cells in coinfected subjects is the adaptation of the schistosome parasite to the definitive host. It has been reported that a female adult worm requires intact host cellmediated immunity for normal egg production. [CITATION_1] Reduced fecundity of schistosome females has been observed in T celldeprived animals. [CITATION_2] This would result in the reduced egg excretion observed in coinfected persons.",
